This is my entry for the next [28mag challenge](https://28-mag.com/2021/01/12/the-28magchallenge-for-2021/).

Beltanya Zukhal is a legal clerc of the Administratum whose task is to record anything and everything, from dead fluotubes to Astra Militarum empty Autocannon cases and daily casualty on the battlefield. She even records the number of downloads of her STL template.
As part of her missions, she frequently goes on field trips to accompany Regimental HQ staff (where she carries a sidearm for self defence).

It is on one of such missions that she met with Inquisitor Johevian of the Ordo Aegis. Now she works for him undercover and has even been sighted with him as part of his retinue.

As always, "Watch" if you want to be informed of any updates.

I remixed this pieces from my [scap box](https://www.thingiverse.com/mangforge/collections/scrap-box):
 + [Laspistol](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3559689)
 + [Gothic dataslate](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4800103)

The Arcadian Interior Guard's specialty is garrison duty. As such, they often make their assigned assignment strong-point more defensible by building a few extra fortification features such as tank traps.

As per tradition, they embed the remains of faithful historical figure in the masonry so even in death every loyal subject of the emperor has a chance to protect the place.

So here you go, a set for Anti-tank concrete obstacles.

I remixed [Brite Minis Skeletons](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3938876) and [Brexitt's](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3273007) and [Cornivius's](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4208870) skulls. Check out what they do :)


As usual "watch" if you want to be alerted if I update this.

item.description:

WIP ! WATCH THIS THING in case of updates.

This is my version of the 1995 bulkheads that were designed for Necromunda (but re-used in latter boxed sets).
They were designed to work with cardboard pieces to create platforms, catwalks and other industrial terrains.

If you are not familiar with the original, there is a video by Kiblams making the apology of this design: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DF_enN4Tz3w]

My version is designed to be printed without support with a PLA printer. It is based on Sirbats' design but with a few adjustments for better printing and new bulkhead feature design.

Without support, the printing is not perfect but tabbletop wortrhy, especially when one is trying to represent a rusty factory underworld.

Hopefully I will make more of these so keep tuned and feel free to give feedbacks !
